{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775862410308,"sessionID":"ses_28660310cffeBZDH9LeLpywe26","part":{"id":"prt_d79a5ebd0001Yxk2ZCTjDIJNEl","messageID":"msg_d79a3a67f001oBR8Hn5BJCycGn","sessionID":"ses_28660310cffeBZDH9LeLpywe26","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-e1c7cffc3a714cc9a5e54c610d29e215","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/design.md","content":"# AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API |\n| Module | `pkg/picod` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nPicoD File Management API provides secure file operations within sandbox pods. It exposes REST endpoints for uploading, listing, and downloading files with workspace jail enforcement, path traversal protection, Base64/multipart upload support, and RS256 JWT authentication. The file API enables AI agents and code interpreters to manage workspace files safely within the sandbox boundary.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### System Context\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                     Kubernetes Cluster                               │\n│  ┌─────────────┐     ┌─────────────┐     ┌─────────────────────────┐│\n│  │   Router    │────▶│  Workload   │────▶│      Sandbox Pod        ││\n│  │ Deployment  │     │   Manager   │     │ ┌─────────────────────┐ ││\n│  │             │     │             │     │ │      PicoD          │ ││\n│  │ JWTManager  │     │ Creates     │     │ │  ┌───────────────┐  │ ││\n│  │ (Private    │     │ Pod +       │     │ │  │ Files API     │  │ ││\n│  │  Key)       │     │ Inject      │     │ │  │               │  │ ││\n│  │             │     │ Public Key  │     │ │  │ UploadFile    │  │ ││\n│  │             │     │ via Env Var │     │ │  │ ListFiles     │  │ ││\n│  │             │     │             │     │ │  │ DownloadFile  │  │ ││\n│  │             │     │             │     │ │  └───────────────┘  │ ││\n│  │             │     │             │     │ │      Workspace      │ ││\n│  │             │     │             │     │ │      (Jail Root)    │ ││\n│  └─────────────┘     └─────────────┘     │ └─────────────────────┘ ││\n│         │                                 └─────────────────────────┘│\n│         │ JWT Token (RS256)                                          │\n│         ▼                                                            │\n│  ┌─────────────┐                                                    │\n│  │   Client    │────▶ Router Proxy ────▶ PicoD /api/files          │\n│  │  (SDK/CLI)  │                                                    │\n│  └─────────────┘                                                    │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Component Diagram\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         PicoD Server                                 │\n│ ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌───────────────────────────┐ │\n│ │   Config    │  │   AuthManager   │  │      Gin Engine           │ │\n│ │ ┌─────────┐ │  │ ┌─────────────┐ │  │ ┌─────────────────────────┐│ │\n│ │ │ Port    │ │  │ │ publicKey   │ │  │ │ Logger Middleware       ││ │\n│ │ │Workspace│ │  │ │ mutex       │ │  │ │ Recovery Middleware     ││ │\n│ │ └─────────┘ │  │ └─────────────┘ │  │ │ AuthMiddleware          ││ │\n│ └─────────────┘  │ AuthMiddleware  │  │ │                         ││ │\n│                  │ LoadPublicKey   │  │ │ /api/files (POST/GET)   ││ │\n│                  └─────────────────┘  │ │ /api/files/*path (GET)  ││ │\n│                                       │ └─────────────────────────┐│ │\n│                                       └───────────────────────────┘ │\n│ ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n│ │                      sanitizePath                                │ │\n│ │   Workspace Jail: symlink resolution, path traversal prevention │ │\n│ └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n│ ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n│ │                   File Operations                                │ │\n│ │   Upload: JSON (Base64) or multipart, parent dir creation        │ │\n│ │   List:   os.ReadDir with FileEntry metadata extraction          │ │\n│ │   Download: MIME type detection, Content-Disposition header      │ │\n│ └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Request Flow\n\n```\nFile Upload Request:\n┌──────────┐    ┌──────────┐    ┌───────────────────────────────────┐\n│  Client  │───▶│  Router  │───▶│            PicoD                  │\n│          │    │          │    │                                   │\n│ POST     │    │ Validate │    │ 1. AuthMiddleware:                │\n│ /api/    │    │ Session  │    │    - Extract Bearer token         │\n│ files    │    │ Generate │    │    - Parse JWT with RS256         │\n│          │    │ JWT      │    │    - Validate expiration          │\n│          │    │          │    │    - Apply MaxBytesReader         │\n│          │    │          │    │                                   │\n│          │    │          │    │ 2. UploadFileHandler:             │\n│          │    │          │    │    - Detect content-type          │\n│          │    │          │    │    - Multipart: extract path+file │\n│          │    │          │    │    - JSON: decode Base64 content  │\n│          │    │          │    │    - sanitizePath(path)           │\n│          │    │          │    │    - parseFileMode(mode)          │\n│          │    │          │    │    - MkdirAll parent dirs         │\n│          │    │          │    │    - WriteFile content            │\n│          │    │          │    │    - Return FileInfo              │\n└──────────┘    └──────────┘    └───────────────────────────────────┘\n\nFile Download Request:\n┌──────────┐    ┌──────────┐    ┌───────────────────────────────────┐\n│  Client  │───▶│  Router  │───▶│            PicoD                  │\n│          │    │          │    │                                   │\n│ GET      │    │ Validate │    │ 1. AuthMiddleware                 │\n│ /api/    │    │ Session  │    │                                   │\n│ files/   │    │ Generate │    │ 2. DownloadFileHandler:           │\n│ <path>   │    │ JWT      │    │    - Extract wildcard path param  │\n│          │    │          │    │    - Trim leading \"/\"             │\n│          │    │          │    │    - sanitizePath(path)           │\n│          │    │          │    │    - os.Stat (check exists+type)  │\n│          │    │          │    │    - MIME type by extension       │\n│          │    │          │    │    - Content-Disposition header   │\n│          │    │          │    │    - c.File(sanitizedPath)        │\n└──────────┘    └──────────┘    └───────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### FileInfo (`pkg/picod/files.go`)\n\n```go\ntype FileInfo struct {\n    Path     string    `json:\"path\"`     // Relative path from workspace\n    Size     int64     `json:\"size\"`     // File size in bytes\n    Mode     string    `json:\"mode\"`     // File mode as octal string (e.g., \"0644\")\n    Modified time.Time `json:\"modified\"` // Last modification time\n}\n```\n\n### UploadFileRequest (`pkg/picod/files.go`)\n\n```go\ntype UploadFileRequest struct {\n    Path    string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`    // Destination path (relative to workspace)\n    Content string `json:\"content\" binding:\"required\"` // Base64-encoded file content\n    Mode    string `json:\"mode\"`                       // Optional octal file mode (e.g., \"0755\")\n}\n```\n\n### FileEntry (`pkg/picod/files.go`)\n\n```go\ntype FileEntry struct {\n    Name     string    `json:\"name\"`     // Entry name (filename or directory name)\n    Size     int64     `json:\"size\"`     // Entry size in bytes\n    Modified time.Time `json:\"modified\"` // Last modification time\n    Mode     string    `json:\"mode\"`     // Entry mode as octal string\n    IsDir    bool      `json:\"is_dir\"`   // Whether entry is a directory\n}\n```\n\n### ListFilesResponse (`pkg/picod/files.go`)\n\n```go\ntype ListFilesResponse struct {\n    Files []FileEntry `json:\"files\"` // Array of file/directory entries\n    Path  string      `json:\"path\"`  // Directory path (relative to workspace)\n}\n```\n\n### Server (`pkg/picod/server.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Server struct {\n    config      *Config               // Server configuration\n    engine      *gin.Engine           // Gin HTTP framework\n    httpServer  *http.Server          // Underlying HTTP server\n    authManager *AuthManager          // JWT authentication manager\n    workspace   string                // Resolved workspace directory (absolute path)\n    startTime   time.Time             // Server start time for uptime tracking\n}\n```\n\n### Constants\n\n| Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n|----------|-------|------|---------|\n| `maxFileMode` | `0777` | `files.go` | Maximum file mode permission (prevent setuid/setgid) |\n| `defaultFileMode` | `0644` | `files.go` | Default file mode when mode invalid/empty |\n| `PublicKeyEnvVar` | `\"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"` | `auth.go` | Environment variable for PEM public key |\n| `MaxBodySize` | `32 << 20` (32 MiB) | `auth.go` | Request body size limit after JWT validation |\n| `version` | `\"0.0.1\"` | `health.go` | PicoD version string |\n| `service` | `\"PicoD\"` | `health.go` | Service name for health response |\n| `readHeaderTimeout` | `10 * time.Second` | `server.go` | HTTP ReadHeaderTimeout |\n\n---\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Endpoints Summary\n\n| Endpoint | Method | Auth | Handler | Description |\n|----------|--------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `/health` | GET | No | `HealthCheckHandler` | Server health status |\n| `/api/files` | POST | JWT | `UploadFileHandler` | Upload file (multipart or JSON) |\n| `/api/files` | GET | JWT | `ListFilesHandler` | List directory contents |\n| `/api/files/*path` | GET | JWT | `DownloadFileHandler` | Download file |\n\n### Upload File (JSON)\n\n**Endpoint**: `POST /api/files`\n\n**Authentication**: JWT Bearer token (RS256)\n\n**Content-Type**: `application/json`\n\n**Request Body**:\n```json\n{\n    \"path\": \"output/result.txt\",\n    \"content\": \"SGVsbG8gV29ybGQ=\",  // Base64-encoded\n    \"mode\": \"0644\"\n}\n```\n\n**Request Fields**:\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `path` | `string` | Yes | Destination path relative to workspace |\n| `content` | `string` | Yes | Base64-encoded file content |\n| `mode` | `string` | No | Octal file mode (default: 0644, max: 0777) |\n\n**Response** (200 OK):\n```json\n{\n    \"path\": \"output/result.txt\",\n    \"size\": 11,\n    \"mode\": \"0644\",\n    \"modified\": \"2026-04-11T10:35:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\n**Error Responses**:\n- 400 Bad Request: Missing path/file, invalid Base64, path escape, invalid mode\n- 401 Unauthorized: Missing/invalid/expired JWT\n- 500 Internal Server Error: Parent directory creation failure, write failure\n\n### Upload File (Multipart)\n\n**Endpoint**: `POST /api/files`\n\n**Authentication**: JWT Bearer token (RS256)\n\n**Content-Type**: `multipart/form-data`\n\n**Form Fields**:\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `path` | `string` | Yes | Destination path |\n| `file` | `file` | Yes | File content |\n| `mode` | `string` | No | Octal file mode |\n\n**Response** (200 OK): Same as JSON upload\n\n### List Files\n\n**Endpoint**: `GET /api/files?path=<directory>`\n\n**Authentication**: JWT Bearer token (RS256)\n\n**Query Parameters**:\n| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |\n|-----------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `path` | `string` | Yes | Directory path to list (relative to workspace) |\n\n**Response** (200 OK):\n```json\n{\n    \"files\": [\n        {\n            \"name\": \"src\",\n            \"size\": 4096,\n            \"modified\": \"2026-04-11T09:00:00Z\",\n            \"mode\": \"0755\",\n            \"is_dir\": true\n        },\n        {\n            \"name\": \"main.py\",\n            \"size\": 1024,\n            \"modified\": \"2026-04-11T10:00:00Z\",\n            \"mode\": \"0644\",\n            \"is_dir\": false\n        }\n    ],\n    \"path\": \"project\"\n}\n```\n\n**Error Responses**:\n- 400 Bad Request: Missing path parameter, path traversal detected\n- 401 Unauthorized: Missing/invalid/expired JWT\n- 500 Internal Server Error: Directory read failure\n\n### Download File\n\n**Endpoint**: `GET /api/files/<path>`\n\n**Authentication**: JWT Bearer token (RS256)\n\n**Path Parameter**: File path relative to workspace (wildcard capture `*path`)\n\n**Response Headers**:\n| Header | Value | Description |\n|--------|-------|-------------|\n| `Content-Type` | MIME type | Detected from file extension (fallback: `application/octet-stream`) |\n| `Content-Disposition` | `attachment; filename=\"<filename>\"` | Download prompt |\n\n**Response**: File content streamed directly via `c.File(sanitizedPath)`\n\n**Error Responses**:\n- 400 Bad Request: Path traversal detected, path is directory\n- 401 Unauthorized: Missing/invalid/expired JWT\n- 404 Not Found: File does not exist\n- 500 Internal Server Error: Stat failure\n\n### Health Check\n\n**Endpoint**: `GET /health`\n\n**Authentication**: None (public endpoint)\n\n**Response** (200 OK):\n```json\n{\n    \"status\": \"ok\",\n    \"service\": \"PicoD\",\n    \"version\": \"0.0.1\",\n    \"uptime\": \"2h30m15s\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### HTTP Status Codes\n\n| Status | Condition |\n|--------|-----------|\n| 200 OK | Successful operation |\n| 400 Bad Request | Invalid request body, missing required fields, path traversal, invalid Base64, invalid mode, path is directory |\n| 401 Unauthorized | Missing Authorization header, invalid JWT, expired token, wrong signing method |\n| 404 Not Found | File not found for download |\n| 500 Internal Server Error | Directory read failure, file write failure, parent directory creation failure, stat failure |\n\n### Error Response Format\n\n```json\n{\n    \"error\": \"<error message>\"\n}\n```\n\n### Authentication Errors\n\n| Condition | HTTP Status | Error Message |\n|-----------|-------------|---------------|\n| Missing Authorization header | 401 | `\"missing authorization header\"` |\n| Invalid token format | 401 | `\"invalid token format\"` |\n| Expired token | 401 | `\"token is expired\"` |\n| Non-RSA signing method | 401 | `\"invalid signing method\"` |\n| Invalid signature | 401 | `\"invalid signature\"` |\n\n### File Upload Errors\n\n| Condition | HTTP Status | Error Message |\n|-----------|-------------|---------------|\n| Missing path parameter | 400 | `\"missing path parameter\"` |\n| Missing file (multipart) | 400 | `\"missing file\"` |\n| Invalid request body | 400 | `\"invalid request body\"` |\n| Path traversal detected | 400 | `\"invalid path: path escape detected\"` |\n| Invalid Base64 content | 400 | `\"invalid base64 content\"` |\n| File mode > 0777 | 400 | `\"invalid file mode\"` |\n| Parent directory creation failure | 500 | `\"failed to create parent directories\"` |\n| File write failure | 500 | `\"failed to write file\"` |\n| Stat failure after write | 500 | `\"failed to get file info\"` |\n\n### File List Errors\n\n| Condition | HTTP Status | Error Message |\n|-----------|-------------|---------------|\n| Missing path parameter | 400 | `\"missing path parameter\"` |\n| Path traversal detected | 400 | `\"invalid path: path escape detected\"` |\n| Directory read failure | 500 | `\"failed to read directory\"` |\n\n### File Download Errors\n\n| Condition | HTTP Status | Error Message |\n|-----------|-------------|---------------|\n| Path traversal detected | 400 | `\"invalid path: path escape detected\"` |\n| Path is directory | 400 | `\"path is not a file\"` |\n| File not found | 404 | `\"file not found\"` |\n| Stat failure | 500 | `\"failed to stat file\"` |\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests (`pkg/picod/picod_test.go`)\n\n#### File Upload Tests\n\n| Test Case | Input | Expected |\n|-----------|-------|----------|\n| Multipart upload | form-data with path=\"upload.txt\", file content | HTTP 200, FileInfo returned, file written |\n| JSON Base64 upload | `{\"path\": \"test.txt\", \"content\": \"dGVzdCBjb250ZW50\"}` | HTTP 200, FileInfo returned, content decoded |\n| Invalid Base64 | `{\"path\": \"test.txt\", \"content\": \"!!invalid\"}` | HTTP 400, \"invalid base64 content\" |\n| Path escape | `{\"path\": \"../escape.txt\", \"content\": \"test\"}` | HTTP 400, \"invalid path\" |\n| Invalid mode (non-octal) | `{\"path\": \"test.txt\", \"content\": \"test\", \"mode\": \"9999\"}` | HTTP 200, uses default 0644 |\n| Mode > 0777 | `{\"path\": \"test.txt\", \"content\": \"test\", \"mode\": \"1000\"}` | HTTP 400, \"invalid file mode\" |\n| Parent directory creation | `{\"path\": \"new/dir/file.txt\", \"content\": \"test\"}` | HTTP 200, parents created with 0755 |\n| Multipart missing path | form-data without path field | HTTP 400, \"missing path parameter\" |\n| Multipart missing file | form-data without file field | HTTP 400, \"missing file\" |\n| File open failure (multipart) | Invalid form file | HTTP 500, \"failed to open file\" |\n| File read failure (multipart) | Read error on form file | HTTP 500, \"failed to read file\" |\n\n#### File List Tests\n\n| Test Case | Input | Expected |\n|-----------|-------|----------|\n| List valid directory | `GET /api/files?path=testdir` (with files) | HTTP 200, FileEntry array |\n| List empty directory | `GET /api/files?path=emptydir` | HTTP 200, empty files array |\n| Missing path parameter | `GET /api/files` | HTTP 400, \"missing path parameter\" |\n| Path escape | `GET /api/files?path=../escape` | HTTP 400, \"invalid path\" |\n| Non-existent directory | `GET /api/files?path=nonexistent` | HTTP 500, \"failed to read directory\" |\n| Entry info failure | Directory with unreadable entry | Skipped (continue), other entries returned |\n\n#### File Download Tests\n\n| Test Case | Input | Expected |\n|-----------|-------|----------|\n| Download existing file | `GET /api/files/testfile.txt` | HTTP 200, file content, correct headers |\n| Download with extension | `GET /api/files/data.json` | Content-Type: application/json |\n| Unknown extension | `GET /api/files/data.xyz` | Content-Type: application/octet-stream |\n| Leading slash stripped | `GET /api/files//absolute.txt` | Resolved correctly |\n| Path escape | `GET /api/files/../escape.txt` | HTTP 400, \"invalid path\" |\n| File not found | `GET /api/files/nonexistent.txt` | HTTP 404, \"file not found\" |\n| Path is directory | `GET /api/files/subdir` | HTTP 400, \"path is not a file\" |\n| Symlink inside workspace | Symlink pointing within workspace | Resolved to target file |\n\n#### Path Sanitization Tests\n\n| Test Case | Input | Expected |\n|-----------|-------|----------|\n| Valid relative path | `\"subdir/file.txt\"` | Absolute path within workspace |\n| Absolute path | `\"/workspace/file.txt\"` | Strips leading `/`, resolves within workspace |\n| Path traversal | `\"../escape.txt\"` | Error: path escape detected |\n| Deep traversal | `\"subdir/../../escape.txt\"` | Error: path escape detected |\n| Existing symlink (safe) | Symlink pointing within workspace | Resolved to target |\n| Null byte injection | `\"file\\x00.txt\"` | Cleaned, safe path within workspace |\n\n#### Authentication Tests\n\n| Test Case | Input | Expected |\n|-----------|-------|----------|\n| Missing header | No Authorization | HTTP 401, \"missing authorization header\" |\n| Invalid format | `Authorization: InvalidFormat` | HTTP 401 |\n| Expired token | JWT with expired `exp` | HTTP 401, \"token is expired\" |\n| HS256 token | JWT signed with HS256 | HTTP 401, \"invalid signing method\" |\n| Valid RS256 token | JWT signed with matching public key | Request proceeds |\n\n#### File Mode Parsing Tests\n\n| Test Case | Input | Expected |\n|-----------|-------|----------|\n| Empty mode | `\"\"` | 0644 (default) |\n| Invalid (non-octal) | `\"invalid\"` | 0644 (default) |\n| Mode > 0777 | `\"1000\"` | Error: \"invalid file mode\" |\n| Valid mode | `\"0755\"` | 0755 |\n\n### Test Helper Functions\n\n```go\nfunc setupTestServer(t *testing.T) *Server       // Creates test server with temp workspace and RSA key\nfunc generateTestJWT(privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey, expired bool) string  // Generates test JWT token\nfunc makeAuthenticatedRequest(t *testing.T, server *Server, method, path string, body io.Reader, contentType string, jwtToken string) *httptest.ResponseRecorder\nfunc encodePublicKeyPEMForTest(key *rsa.PublicKey) string\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n| Test Scenario | Description |\n|---------------|-------------|\n| Full file lifecycle | Upload file → List directory → Download file → Verify content matches |\n| Auth key mismatch | Router uses different key pair → PicoD rejects token |\n| Large file upload | File approaching 32 MiB limit |\n| Concurrent operations | Multiple upload/download requests in parallel |\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\npkg/picod/\n├── config.go           # Config struct definition (Port, Workspace)\n├── server.go           # Server struct, NewServer, Run, Shutdown, route registration\n├── auth.go             # AuthManager, LoadPublicKeyFromEnv, AuthMiddleware\n├── execute.go          # ExecuteRequest, ExecuteResponse, ExecuteHandler (AR-015)\n├── files.go            # FileInfo, UploadFileRequest, FileEntry, ListFilesResponse, file handlers\n├── health.go           # HealthCheckHandler, version/service constants\n├── sanitize.go         # sanitizePath function for workspace jail security\n├── picod_test.go       # Unit tests for all handlers\n└── doc.go              # Package documentation\n\ncmd/picod/\n└── main.go             # Entry point with CLI flag parsing, klog initialization\n```\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | v1.10+ | HTTP framework, route registration, middleware, JSON binding, multipart form handling |\n| `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | v5.2+ | JWT parsing, RSA signing method validation, leeway/expiry options |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Existing | CLI flag registration, structured logging, fatal error handling |\n| `crypto/rsa` | Standard | RSA public key type |\n| `crypto/x509` | Standard | PKIX public key parsing |\n| `encoding/pem` | Standard | PEM block decoding |\n| `encoding/base64` | Standard | Base64 decoding for JSON file upload |\n| `os` | Standard | File operations: WriteFile, Stat, ReadDir, MkdirAll |\n| `path/filepath` | Standard | Path cleaning, symlink resolution, relative path computation, base extraction |\n| `mime` | Standard | `mime.TypeByExtension` for download Content-Type |\n| `strconv` | Standard | `ParseUint` for octal file mode parsing |\n| `strings` | Standard | Path prefix stripping, trimming |\n| `time` | Standard | Time handling for FileInfo.Modified |\n| `io` | Standard | `io.ReadAll` for multipart file content |\n| `mime/multipart` | Standard | Multipart form parsing |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n### Upload Handler Flow (JSON)\n\n```go\nfunc (s *Server) UploadFileHandler(c *gin.Context) {\n    contentType := c.ContentType()\n    \n    // Detect content type\n    if contentType == \"multipart/form-data\" {\n        // Multipart handling\n        path = c.PostForm(\"path\")\n        fileHeader, _ := c.FormFile(\"file\")\n        file, _ := fileHeader.Open()\n        content, _ = io.ReadAll(file)\n        modeStr = c.PostForm(\"mode\")\n    } else {\n        // JSON handling\n        var req UploadFileRequest\n        c.ShouldBindJSON(&req)\n        path = req.Path\n        decoded, _ = base64.StdEncoding.DecodeString(req.Content)\n        content = decoded\n        modeStr = req.Mode\n    }\n    \n    // Sanitize path\n    sanitizedPath, err := sanitizePath(s.workspace, path)\n    \n    // Parse file mode\n    mode, err := parseFileMode(modeStr)\n    \n    // Create parent directories\n    parentDir := filepath.Dir(sanitizedPath)\n    os.MkdirAll(parentDir, 0755)\n    \n    // Write file\n    os.WriteFile(sanitizedPath, content, mode)\n    \n    // Return FileInfo\n    info, _ := os.Stat(sanitizedPath)\n    c.JSON(200, FileInfo{...})\n}\n```\n\n### List Handler Flow\n\n```go\nfunc (s *Server) ListFilesHandler(c *gin.Context) {\n    path := c.Query(\"path\")\n    \n    // Sanitize path\n    sanitizedPath, err := sanitizePath(s.workspace, path)\n    \n    // Read directory\n    entries, err := os.ReadDir(sanitizedPath)\n    \n    // Build FileEntry array\n    files := []FileEntry{}\n    for _, entry := range entries {\n        info, err := entry.Info()\n        if err != nil {\n            continue  // Skip entries with stat errors\n        }\n        files = append(files, FileEntry{\n            Name:     entry.Name(),\n            Size:     info.Size(),\n            Modified: info.ModTime(),\n            Mode:     fmt.Sprintf(\"%04o\", info.Mode().Perm()),\n            IsDir:    entry.IsDir(),\n        })\n    }\n    \n    c.JSON(200, ListFilesResponse{Files: files, Path: path})\n}\n```\n\n### Download Handler Flow\n\n```go\nfunc (s *Server) DownloadFileHandler(c *gin.Context) {\n    reqPath := c.Param(\"path\")\n    reqPath = strings.TrimPrefix(reqPath, \"/\")\n    \n    // Sanitize path\n    sanitizedPath, err := sanitizePath(s.workspace, reqPath)\n    \n    // Check file exists and is not directory\n    info, err := os.Stat(sanitizedPath)\n    if info.IsDir() {\n        c.JSON(400, gin.H{\"error\": \"path is not a file\"})\n        return\n    }\n    \n    // Detect MIME type\n    contentType := mime.TypeByExtension(filepath.Ext(sanitizedPath))\n    if contentType == \"\" {\n        contentType = \"application/octet-stream\"\n    }\n    \n    // Set headers\n    filename := filepath.Base(sanitizedPath)\n    c.Header(\"Content-Type\", contentType)\n    c.Header(\"Content-Disposition\", fmt.Sprintf(\"attachment; filename=\\\"%s\\\"\", filename))\n    \n    // Stream file\n    c.File(sanitizedPath)\n}\n```\n\n### File Mode Parsing\n\n```go\nfunc parseFileMode(modeStr string) (os.FileMode, error) {\n    if modeStr == \"\" {\n        return defaultFileMode, nil  // 0644\n    }\n    \n    mode, err := strconv.ParseUint(modeStr, 8, 32)\n    if err != nil {\n        return defaultFileMode, nil  // Invalid → use default\n    }\n    \n    if mode > maxFileMode {  // 0777\n        return 0, errors.New(\"invalid file mode\")\n    }\n    \n    return os.FileMode(mode), nil\n}\n```\n\n**Mode Constraints**:\n- Max value: `0777` (prevents setuid/setgid/sticky bits)\n- Invalid/non-octal strings fall back to `0644`\n- Mode > `0777` returns error (reject request)\n\n### Route Registration Pattern\n\n```go\nfunc NewServer(config *Config) (*Server, error) {\n    // ...\n    engine.GET(\"/health\", s.HealthCheckHandler)\n    \n    api := engine.Group(\"/api\")\n    api.Use(s.authManager.AuthMiddleware())\n    {\n        api.POST(\"/execute\", s.ExecuteHandler)   // AR-015\n        api.POST(\"/files\", s.UploadFileHandler)  // AR-016\n        api.GET(\"/files\", s.ListFilesHandler)    // AR-016\n        api.GET(\"/files/*path\", s.DownloadFileHandler)  // AR-016\n    }\n    // ...\n}\n```\n\n### Path Sanitization Algorithm\n\nThe `sanitizePath` function enforces workspace jail security:\n\n1. Resolve workspace directory (follow symlinks to get canonical path)\n2. Clean requested path (`filepath.Clean`)\n3. Strip leading `/` if absolute\n4. Join with workspace root\n5. Check relative path doesn't start with `..` (path traversal)\n6. If path exists, re-validate after symlink resolution\n7. Return resolved, safe absolute path\n\n### MIME Type Detection\n\nUses `mime.TypeByExtension(filepath.Ext(path))`:\n- Common extensions: `.json` → `application/json`, `.txt` → `text/plain`\n- Unknown extensions: fallback to `application/octet-stream`\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- `changes/AR-015/design.md` — PicoD Execute API design (shared architecture)\n- `deployment/client-go.md` — Kubernetes client for sandbox pod configuration\n- `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` — `AuthModePicoD` constant\n- `pkg/router/jwt.go` — Router JWT issuance (key pair generation)\n- `pkg/router/errors.go` — Router error types pattern\n- `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` — HTTP server lifecycle pattern\n- [github.com/gin-gonic/gin](https://github.com/gin-gonic/gin) — Gin framework\n- [github.com/golang-jwt/jwt](https://github.com/golang-jwt/jwt) — JWT library\n- [Go mime package](https://pkg.go.dev/mime) — MIME type detection"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/picod/files.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/picod/server.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/picod/doc.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/picod/health.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/picod/sanitize.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/picod/auth.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":87,"character":63},"end":{"line":87,"character":74}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interfa